folder: Minetta Lane & MacDougal Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Minetta Lane, north side, from but not including MacDougal Street, west to the intersection of Sixth Ave., and Carmine Street. This lane will soon be modernized. 1923.

Gift of E. M. Jenks.

folder: Minetta Lane & MacDougal Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Minetta Lane, from MacDougal Street, to the intersection of Sixth Ave. and Carmine Street, showing a modern paved street with several new buildings.
About 1925.

folder: MacDougal Street & Minetta Lane, Manhattan, NY
text:
115, 117 Macdougal Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Minetta Lane, south of West 3rd (formerly Amity) Street. No. 115 is (obviously) an old stable. Notice the beam projecting over the tall upper window in the center. A pulley was fastened to this so that bales of hay could be hoisted up into the hayloft.
May 23, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
